content.description:
Start in a horizontal that is a bit on the low side and work up fun hueco seams that yield jugs. Leading to a thin move about 10 feet up. Another long move leads to the angling crack high on the face and an easier top out. 

  The landing has 2 tiers so padding both and having a good spot would be a good idea if you think you might come off.
content.location: As you approach the Maze from between the Spur and West Mountain you will see the wall with the problems before you enter the rocks. This is the right hand problem on the face.

content.description: Start kind of low, you could probably sit. Climb up on nice hueco flakes that are mostly side pulls until you reach the angling crack across the top of the face. From here things get easier to the top.
content.location: As you approach the Maze from between the Spur and West Mountain you will see the wall with the problems before you enter the rocks. This is the left hand line on the wall.

content.description: Used to start on a fist sized hueco with a good edge in the bottom (since broken, by my over weight self, leaving a bruised elbow). Start above the hueco on some slopers. Traverse right on slopers with small feet until you reach some mail slots. continue right and up on the slots to an easy top out.
content.location: As you approach the Maze from between the Spur and West Mountain you will see a wall with a couple of nice easy problems on it before you enter the rocks. This problem is in a corridor to the left of this wall.

content.description: On the left side of the Ten Foot Wall, sit start on large huecos and move up a series of huecos and good holds directly up the face of the boulder.
content.location: On the left side of the Ten Foot Wall, left of Clumsy Plumber

content.description: Stand start to Meatmaker.
content.location: Around the corner right of Better Eat Your Wheaties.

climbs.name: This Is Your Brain On Drugs

content.description: Climbs in the dihedral of Dihedral Rock. Start on crimps at the bottom of the dihedral with your feet on a decent rail.
content.location: Very obvious dihedral on the Dihedral Rock boulder.

content.description: Located on the leftmost arête of the Ten Foot Wall Boulder, sit start on the jug rail and climb the arête and move out right along the lip and top out.
content.location: Located on the leftmost arête of the Ten Foot Wall Boulder

content.description: Start in the giant Hueco and figure out how to catch the sharp crimp jug up and to the right. Move on sharp jugs trending further right and top out.
content.location: The obvious giant Hueco in the middle; right of Flexin' Texan and left of Italy Overthrown.

content.description: Tall slabby fun
content.location: in the warmup area tall slab, start on a low boulder

content.description: Scary highball slab up and to the right of Jigsaw Puzzle.  You have to be a slab master for this one!

Good rock, nice holds, engaging top out are all good things. The hardest move right off the ground would normally be bad but with the poor landing is probably a plus as well. 

  Start on some small holds and explode up to a flat jug. float the jugs up and left to a hueco. Then head up past a spooky looking block to a sloping lip encounter.
content.location: Start to the right of the block that sits behind the Godzillatron Boulder on a right sloping undercling and a left edge in a shallow corner. From the main Maze area head through the boulders away from East Mountain under Wheaties to the boulder behind.

content.description: Starts around the corner to the right from Wheaties in a big Hueco.  A big throw to the right gains the "meat hook" hold.  Continue right and upwards to a balancy, scary topout.  In the sun most of the day.

Crux is the last move of this climb.  Maybe better rated as 5.12 a/b.  Begin down and left of the obvious chalked ending.  Weave your way through varried and fun moves to the end.  The dyno is SICK.  Don't be afraid to go for it as you land safe and sound onto the boulder behind every time.  Nice to have a chalkbag on this one.
content.protection: One pad and an attentive spotter.
content.location: Walk into The Maze proper, past Better Eat Your Wheaties and Meat Maker.  Jingus Bells is two boulders further walking straight through.  The landing in on the boulder behind the top out.  The climb begins way down and left of the topout.  Have fun.

content.description: One of the best V5s, this problem starts at the right side of a face that resembles a jigsaw puzzle. Climb the boulder from left to right trending upwards and toping out on the right side of the boulder.

Sweet traverse on jugs, would be worthy of 4 stars if dabbing halfway through was not an issue. 

  Head right from the low jugs near the middle of the wall.start out traversing more or less along the lip at one point using a hold under the lip. Eventually move up into a good left hand sidepull half pocket and make a long reach out right to an undercling, match your left foot to hand as either a toe or heal toe and drop your left down to a good seem. Now for the anti dab first crux, release the foot and swing onto the hand holds with a smear for your right foot. The rest of the problem is tough enduro climbing, big moves on bigish holds. Bump your left further along the seam and make a long move out right to the left end of another seam with a flat hold that sort of tilts toward you. Get a right heal hook and match up to make another long move right to a better hold. Some consider this the end of the problem but for full credit top it out, the climbing is easier but not neseccarily a gimmie, I've seen someone pitch from above here.
content.location: Standing in the clearing between the Maze and main spur, there is a large wave like boulder to your right with next to no holds up high but loads of holds down low. Start at low holds near the middle of the face where the boulder is undercut in a horizontal roof and climb right to the arete and up.

content.description:
Move up and left into some pockets that can be sidepulled. There are a couple of sloping terrible holds between here and the next good hold that you can use but don't have to. Some how reach out to the good straight down pulling hold from the pockets then heal hook one of the other pockets by your right hand and lever up to an OK edge for your right about 3 feet above your left but not quite as far over. This position allows you to cut the heal and hold the swing. Once under control, campus down onto the good hold and left a couple of moves to the drop off jug. 

  I have not heard of anyone topping this line out so the drop off is pressumed legit.
content.protection: Pads and spotters, if you blow cutting your feet it is going to be exciting and you will land way, way out left, not recommended.
content.location: On the same boulder as Javalina starting in the same low jugs near the middle of the face and traverse left to the end of the wall.

content.description: "Jump to a good hold at about 8 ft. Then go right and up to the lip"
content.location: Right side of Godzillatron boulder, to the right boulder that forms landing for Jingus Bells. Look for obvious high starting hold shelf.

content.description: Climb up and finish right.
content.location: On Dihedral rock, to the right of bildo.

content.description: Starts in a scoop on the arete to the right of Better Eat Your Wheaties and traverses left on impossibly small crimps to finish on Wheaties.
Stand start on the "bad landing" Boulder and move up tiny pinches to a high heady, sloper. Finish on big holds above the sloper.
content.location: To the right of Gangbanging That Wide Crack, the leftmost climb on the Slim Pickins Face Boulder.

content.description: Sit start on good huecos and move up along the arête on large holds to the top
content.location: On the Ten Foot Wall boulder. When facing the boulder, it is the rightmost problem and starts on/near the arête.

content.description: on the ten foot wall, one of the more fun warm-ups
content.protection: pad, watch out for boulder below landing
content.location: in between the main warm up boulder and jigsaw

content.description:
A classic crimp problem, Because of the nature of the holds this problem really is not all that height dependant. 

  From the start side pull get your feet on, either a good right or both, or a high left depending on your preference. If you are small bury the left hand side pull, if big, crush it for all your worth. Reach or bump your way up to a sharp edge that is some what of a gaston. Move your feet around and reach the pinch right at the lip. From here there are several ways to finish, and the next move or two are the crux. However you do it you will be tic-tacing your way up some pretty small holds that are on a vertical wall while your feet are still on the overhang.   

  To top out move left in the horizontal below the next over hanging panel and up at a flake at mid-height on this next overhanging panel. This is easier that the rest of the problem but it never hurts to have a look in advance just to see where those top out holds are over the lip. 

Location

  From the meadow between the Maze and East Mt head throught the tunnel formed by the big boulder that is furthest to the left and the short wall to the right, when you get through you will be looking at an overhung wall that has lots of chalk and features. This one starts high on a good left-hand sidepull and right-hand crimper/gaston, in the middle/right of the face where there is another rock behind the steep face.
Good warmup for the Maze
content.location: Tall face of the Dihedral Rock

content.description: Climb the crack between the Ten Foot Wall Boulder and the Slim Pickins Face Boulder.
content.location: Located between the Ten Foot Wall Boulder and the Slim Pickins Face Boulder.

content.description: Crux is the very top.  Throw from the Right hand sloper and left hand pocket to the sloping lip.  Nice flat landing so just go for it.  No small holds on this one.
content.location: Left of Better Eat Your Wheaties.  Starts in a big flake with a long move to the seam that goes across the entire boulder at mid height.

content.description:
A very popular area now that the guide tour system is the only way to acces the "back country". Lots of problems in a relatively small area. Good warm ups which makes it a popular first stop for tours and a good bunch of harder problems to work on depending upon ones abilities, worthy projects from V5 to V13. 

  Classics include:(this list includes the back of the maze as well)   Jingus Bells V5+   Better Eat Your Wheaties V8-9   Crown of Aragorn V13   Jigsaw Puzzle V5   Javalina V8+   Glas Roof V9   The Egg V9   Nagual V13   Flower Power V10-11
